  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to be directed to a public chat when scanning a QR code representing the public chat's universal link so that I may participate in the public chat.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\nCurrently, the status QR code scanner returns an \"unable to read this code\" when scanning a QR code derived from a public chat universal link. https://wiki.status.im/Universal_Links.\r\n\r\n![screenshot_20180808-080403_status](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7915365/43826671-ca087b74-9aef-11e8-992f-7c2c1fda9a84.jpg)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nIt is expected that when a QR code derived from a public chat unviersal link is scanned by a status user by following the path \"+\" -> \"start new chat\" -> \"qr code symbol\" the user is taken to the public chat. \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nWhen a public chat QR code is scanned, it returns an \"unable to read this code\" error pop up. \r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- On Status chat page tap on the \"+\" button. \r\n- Then tap on \"start new chat\"\r\n- Then tap on the \"QR code symbol\" top the right of \"enter contact code\". \r\n- Then attempt scanning a QR code generated from a public chat unviersal link. \r\n\r\nFor example attempt scanning this code generated from ETHIndia public chat group. \r\n![ethindia-1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7915365/43826917-6a81cf10-9af0-11e8-9beb-f7817d82d015.png)\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\nEssentailly the public chat universal link format needs to be read as valid by the status QR code scanner when activated via the \"start new chat\" path. \r\n\n\n<blockquote><img src=\"/favicon.ico\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div><strong><a href=\"https://wiki.status.im/Universal_Links\">Universal Links - Status Wiki</a></strong></div></blockquote>",
